NCAA Division III Logo
NCAA Division III is a division of the National Collegiate Athletic Association in the United States. DIII consists of athletic programs at colleges and universities that choose not to offer athletic scholarships to their student-athletes. The NCAA’s first split was into two divisions, the University and College Divisions, in 1956, the College Division was formed for smaller schools that did not have the resources of the major athletic programs across the country.
